definition.value: An aromatic amino acid that is anthranilic acid in which one of the hydrogens attached to the nitrogen is substituted by a methyl group.
An N-acetoxyarylamine having 1,1'-biphenyl-4-amine as the arylamine component.
The simplest monocarboxylic acid amide, obtained by formal condensation of formic acid with ammonia. The parent of the class of formaldehydes.
